The MCN Corporation, a natural-gas holding company, said yesterday that its subsidiaries had agreed to buy gas- and oil-related properties in six states for a total of $120 million. MCN said that the purchase included gas producing and pipeline properties in Virginia from Consol Coal Group. The acquisition includes a 100 percent interest in 130 producing wells and rights to undertake additional development drilling on about 100,000 acres of Virginia coal bed properties. MCN also agreed to buy gas and oil properties in Texas, Oklahoma, Kansas, Colorado and North Dakota.